Status report of Yi Tong Tse on 5/15/00

NCTA Show

The show was on last week.  Because one of the two rateMux boxes that we sent
has (hardward?) problem, we set up the remaining one and run the dpi code on it
for both the rateMux and dpi demo.  The dpi demo was quite successful, but
for the ratemux demo, some channels lost video after several hours.  

After talking to the people who went to the show, I collected the following
action items that we need to address:

- Need to do more testing of the dpi code in ratemux mode (eventually the
  dpi code will replace the ratemux code in the future.)

- Need to add black frame insertion to dpi
  (The latest API added a field which may request black frames at end of
   the ad.)

- Need to improve dpi's error handling capability (that is, when the input
  bitstream has errors in it.)

Some work has been done to address the last issue.  We have updated our
requant module with the latest version from the ratemux code because it
has much better error handling.  However, we found that the improvement
will not work for some cases when the bitstream contains field pictures.
Wayne Lee is working on the fix.

I have also added some code to dpi to disregard the rate conversion request
when we detect errors in a picture.

I am also in the process of rewriting part of the bitstream parsing core
routines to remove some unnecessary assumptions as well as some bugs which
may cause the code to die.


DPI Development

We managed to reproduce in our lab the vertical sync problem that SeaChange
reported.  The symptom is that with GI's DCT 1000 setop box, the upper part
of the picture is unstable when we run the dpi code.  The problem disappears
when we run ratemux code.  However, after we do some more tests, we found out
that the real reason is that for some reason, the GI setop box cannot handle
bitstreams whose picture header is aligned with PES header.  This aligned
picture header is one particular case in MPEG stream, and is actually required
in ATSC version.  We will try to see whether the same problem appears in
newer versions of setop boxes, while at the same time I am working on modifying
the output bitstream to avoid such problem.

I have fixed a bug in sequence end code insertion in the splice point.
I also found and fixed a bug which causes dpi code the hang when the
statmux clock and the dpi clock are out of sync.

